               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18341124-name-491" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18341124-name-491" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18341124-name-491" type="surname" value="WALLIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18341124-name-491" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WALLIS</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 24th of November, I was at the foot of London Bridge, about half-past four o'clock—I felt some one at my pocket—I turned, and saw the prisoner putting my handkerchief into his breeches pocket—I accused him of having it—he said, "Here it is, Sir," and ran away—I followed him—he crossed the road, ran down the steps, crossed</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183411240070"></xptr>
               <p>again, and ran up the steps on the other side—I did not lose sight of him till he was stopped.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I picked it up, and when the gentleman asked me, I gave it him. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I am quite sure he took it from my pocket, and when I took him he begged for mercy.</p>
